name: object-get
description: Gets properties from objects with a path expression.
readme: [![view on npm](http://img.shields.io/npm/v/object-get.svg)](https://www.npmjs.org/package/object-get) [![npm module downloads per month](http://img.shields.io/npm/dm/object-get.svg)](https://www.npmjs.org/package/object-get) [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/75lb/object-get.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/75lb/object-get) [![Dependency Status](https://david-dm.org/75lb/object-get.svg)](https://david-dm.org/75lb/object-get) [![js-standard-style](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-standard-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/feross/standard) ## object-get Gets a value for a property path. **Example** ```js var objectGet = require("object-get") ``` ### objectGet(object, expression) ⇒ \* ⏏ Returns the value at the given property. **Kind**: Exported function | Param | Type | Description | | --- | --- | --- | | object | object | the input object | | expression | string | the property accessor expression | * * * © 2015 Lloyd Brookes \<75pound@gmail.com\>.
